1
00:00:01,170 --> 00:00:03,540
(Episode 89)

2
00:00:14,350 --> 00:00:15,350
I'm sorry.

3
00:00:15,920 --> 00:00:17,290
I'm sorry, Baek Ho.

4
00:00:18,560 --> 00:00:22,160
You were the best man, my first love.

5
00:00:23,330 --> 00:00:26,530
My love, you'll live in my heart forever.

6
00:00:27,870 --> 00:00:30,300
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

7
00:00:32,940 --> 00:00:36,140
- Hello?
- Jang Mi, it's me. You missed me, right?

8
00:00:37,980 --> 00:00:38,980
Baek Ho.

9
00:00:39,540 --> 00:00:43,350
- Let's go on a date.
- Oh my goodness.

10
00:00:43,680 --> 00:00:47,220
You're asking me out for a change.
I feel great!

11
00:00:47,720 --> 00:00:49,550
In that case, I'll plan our date.

12
00:00:49,790 --> 00:00:53,160
Then I'll have to
pack something really good, too.

13
00:00:53,160 --> 00:00:54,490
See you Saturday.

14
00:00:54,930 --> 00:00:57,330
I'm so excited for our date.
It's been a while.

15
00:00:58,400 --> 00:00:59,560
I love you, Jang Mi.

16
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:02,200
Me too...

17
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:06,470
I'm at the office.
I have to go. Bye, Baek Ho.

18
00:01:10,110 --> 00:01:13,310
I love you too, Baek Ho.

19
00:01:14,310 --> 00:01:15,480
More than anyone in the world...

20
00:01:16,480 --> 00:01:19,880
No, I love you more than my own life,
Baek Ho.

21
00:01:25,460 --> 00:01:27,160
I can't tell you that your brother,
Kang Jun Ho...

22
00:01:27,960 --> 00:01:30,600
is Chae Hwa Young's secret son.

23
00:01:31,760 --> 00:01:34,370
You'll be devastated enough
when I break up with you.

24
00:01:35,700 --> 00:01:37,040
If you find out about this too...

25
00:01:38,870 --> 00:01:40,210
I'm so sorry, Baek Ho.

26
00:01:44,710 --> 00:01:45,740
What?

27
00:01:46,110 --> 00:01:48,410
You're saying Kang Jun Ho
is Chae Hwa Young's son?

28
00:01:49,050 --> 00:01:51,820
Kang Jun Ho is
Baek Ho's older brother, right?

29
00:01:51,820 --> 00:01:52,920
That's right.

30
00:01:54,150 --> 00:01:57,720
- Anyway, we have to keep it from Baek Ho.
- This is unbelievable.

31
00:01:58,720 --> 00:02:02,390
Wait, so Chae Hwa Young had a kid
even before she stole Seo Rin?

32
00:02:04,460 --> 00:02:07,270
She's a mother herself!
How could she have done that to my mom?

33
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:08,730
That woman's a thief. A complete thief.

34
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:11,940
This is good, though.

35
00:02:12,040 --> 00:02:15,570
Suk Hee likes spicy stir-fried chicken
and steamed eggs too.

36
00:02:15,740 --> 00:02:17,240
Grandma, me too!

37
00:02:18,680 --> 00:02:20,040
Here.

38
00:02:22,750 --> 00:02:25,580
We also have rice balls
and cold acorn jelly soup.

39
00:02:26,150 --> 00:02:29,950
There's plenty for Bo Ra to eat
when she can't handle spicy food.

40
00:02:31,190 --> 00:02:32,920
This place is really good.

41
00:02:33,990 --> 00:02:35,860
Eating it in these wraps
is a nice change of pace.

42
00:02:36,190 --> 00:02:38,030
It goes so well
with the spicy stir-fried chicken.

43
00:02:38,760 --> 00:02:41,070
Isn't it nice to eat comfortably at home?

44
00:02:41,570 --> 00:02:42,770
Good call getting takeout, right?

45
00:02:44,500 --> 00:02:45,700
I just feel bad for Jang Mi.

46
00:02:46,470 --> 00:02:49,070
She's marrying Kang Jun Ho
just to get revenge on Chae Hwa Young,

47
00:02:49,340 --> 00:02:50,640
and you're all talking about
how good the food is?

48
00:02:51,740 --> 00:02:52,740
Darn it.

49
00:02:54,210 --> 00:02:56,880
So what? Good food is good food.
What do you want me to do about it?

50
00:02:58,180 --> 00:02:59,650
You've made the right decision, Jun Ho.

51
00:03:00,290 --> 00:03:04,220
- That's my boy.
- My marriage has nothing to do with you.

52
00:03:04,890 --> 00:03:06,120
So don't get too excited.

53
00:03:06,390 --> 00:03:09,590
Have you forgotten
that I'm Seo Rin's mother?

54
00:03:09,890 --> 00:03:11,660
Yes, Mother-in-law.

55
00:03:12,730 --> 00:03:13,800
You're my mother-in-law.

56
00:03:14,770 --> 00:03:16,900
Nothing more, nothing less.

57
00:03:17,570 --> 00:03:19,840
So don't get any ideas
about me being your son.

58
00:03:20,100 --> 00:03:21,840
- Jun Ho.
- Not even in your wildest dreams...

59
00:03:22,110 --> 00:03:24,210
should you dare think of me as your son.

60
00:03:25,240 --> 00:03:26,380
Because if you ever do,

61
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:30,850
no matter how much I love Jang Mi,
I'll call off this wedding in a heartbeat.

62
00:03:31,480 --> 00:03:32,520
So the choice is yours.

63
00:03:33,250 --> 00:03:35,090
Fine, I get it.

64
00:03:36,020 --> 00:03:39,290
I'll never tell anyone you're my son.
I swear.

65
00:03:39,390 --> 00:03:43,930
In fact, I'm the one who's most terrified
of that secret getting out.

66
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:46,970
- That's not the point.
- I said I get it.

67
00:03:55,970 --> 00:03:56,980
Honey.

68
00:03:58,180 --> 00:04:00,580
I heard you were feeling sick.
Are you any better now?

69
00:04:01,150 --> 00:04:02,150
Yes.

70
00:04:02,150 --> 00:04:05,420
Where are you off to? The hospital?
Do you want me to drive?

71
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:07,850
No. Just to get some fresh air.

72
00:04:08,090 --> 00:04:11,090
You want to get some air?
You should be going to the hospital.

73
00:04:11,090 --> 00:04:12,360
Do you want to get sicker?

74
00:04:14,190 --> 00:04:16,190
You're being so strange.

75
00:04:17,160 --> 00:04:20,630
Both kids are on board,
and Chairman Ma's family is happy with it.

76
00:04:21,230 --> 00:04:22,700
So why the long face?

77
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:27,210
- What are you talking about?
- Why are you the only one against it?

78
00:04:27,510 --> 00:04:30,240
Our son is going through with a marriage
I'm against.

79
00:04:30,510 --> 00:04:31,680
How am I supposed to be happy about it?

80
00:04:31,780 --> 00:04:36,250
Then give me a convincing reason
for why you're against it.

81
00:04:37,250 --> 00:04:40,690
You always put the kids first.

82
00:04:41,790 --> 00:04:45,860
This is a good thing for Jun Ho,
so why are you fighting it?

83
00:04:45,920 --> 00:04:49,490
Does marrying a rich family
guarantee happiness?

84
00:04:50,090 --> 00:04:54,370
Our son is going to live with her family.
Are you happy about that?

85
00:04:54,670 --> 00:04:57,740
Come on. After all the hard work
we put into raising him,

86
00:04:57,900 --> 00:04:59,000
he’s going to be a live-in son-in-law?
Unbelievable.

87
00:04:59,070 --> 00:05:00,870
It’s not just any family.

88
00:05:00,870 --> 00:05:03,140
He'll be a live-in son-in-law
for Dream Group.

89
00:05:04,180 --> 00:05:08,050
Our Jun Ho could end up
becoming the Chairman of Dream one day.

90
00:05:08,110 --> 00:05:11,280
Dream on.
Don't you know how Chairman Ma is?

91
00:05:11,280 --> 00:05:12,280
You're so naive.

92
00:05:12,420 --> 00:05:13,520
Anyway...

93
00:05:14,450 --> 00:05:17,320
If you care about your son's future,
you need to stop opposing this.

94
00:05:17,390 --> 00:05:20,430
Forget it. I'm not changing my mind.

95
00:05:21,360 --> 00:05:22,360
What?

96
00:05:23,090 --> 00:05:25,000
What's wrong with him?

97
00:05:25,660 --> 00:05:28,470
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

98
00:05:30,070 --> 00:05:33,270
Has Professor Kang said anything?

99
00:05:34,470 --> 00:05:36,070
What? About what?

100
00:05:36,340 --> 00:05:38,240
Did he approve of their marriage?

101
00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:43,250
Isn't Professor Kang suspicious
about Oh Bok Gil's death?

102
00:05:43,480 --> 00:05:47,850
It's fine. I'll have to talk him down.
If not, Jun Ho will handle it.

103
00:05:48,150 --> 00:05:50,760
And that Oh Jang Mi surrendered so easily
doesn't sit right with me either.

104
00:05:51,160 --> 00:05:52,720
What choice did she have?

105
00:05:53,090 --> 00:05:56,330
To save Kang Baek Ho and Seo Rin,
surrendering was her only option.

106
00:05:56,890 --> 00:06:01,100
Regardless, we can't let
Oh Jang Mi find Seo Rin.

107
00:06:02,030 --> 00:06:03,030
Of course.

108
00:06:03,970 --> 00:06:07,310
Seo Rin still has no signs of waking up?

109
00:06:07,910 --> 00:06:09,140
No, not yet.

110
00:06:10,640 --> 00:06:13,210
Keep a close watch on her,
and whatever you do, don't get caught.

111
00:06:29,460 --> 00:06:31,860
Come on in.

112
00:06:32,930 --> 00:06:35,430
So, how are you feeling?
I heard you got hurt.

113
00:06:35,670 --> 00:06:36,800
I'm all right now, Chairman.

114
00:06:37,140 --> 00:06:39,440
Good. Let's go to my study.

115
00:06:39,770 --> 00:06:40,770
Yes, Chairman.

116
00:06:43,670 --> 00:06:44,680
Oh my.

117
00:06:45,640 --> 00:06:46,810
I wonder what they're going to talk about.

118
00:06:53,890 --> 00:06:57,090
I need to make some changes to my will.

119
00:06:59,220 --> 00:07:00,220
May I ask why?

120
00:07:02,390 --> 00:07:03,460
I'm curious...

121
00:07:04,560 --> 00:07:07,930
if you're going to be loyal to Seo Rin.

122
00:07:08,300 --> 00:07:09,530
That's what I want to know.

123
00:07:10,870 --> 00:07:13,340
I can assure you I'm not one
of CEO Chae's people.

124
00:07:13,670 --> 00:07:15,040
I see.

125
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:18,640
I asked to see you...

126
00:07:19,180 --> 00:07:22,850
because I'd like you to be
my left-hand man from now on.

127
00:07:24,180 --> 00:07:27,420
- Excuse me?
- When you lose your right arm, you bleed,

128
00:07:27,590 --> 00:07:30,320
but you lose your balance
without your left arm.

129
00:07:31,060 --> 00:07:34,130
There will be many changes
concerning me in the near future.

130
00:07:34,690 --> 00:07:35,690
And when that happens,

131
00:07:36,490 --> 00:07:39,700
I'd like to count on your support.
What do you say?

132
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:42,200
It would be my honor, Chairman.

133
00:07:43,700 --> 00:07:44,700
Good.

134
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:46,400
Then, first of all,

135
00:07:47,810 --> 00:07:51,540
I'd like to make some changes to my will.

136
00:07:52,210 --> 00:07:53,280
What changes would you like to make?

137
00:07:56,110 --> 00:07:59,080
No matter who ends up with my Seo Rin,

138
00:08:00,350 --> 00:08:03,790
change it so they can't inherit more
than three percent of the shares.

139
00:08:04,390 --> 00:08:07,390
- Yes, sir.
- Even if Seo Rin gets married,

140
00:08:07,790 --> 00:08:11,500
no one must be allowed to take her place.

141
00:08:11,760 --> 00:08:13,970
- Do you understand?
- Yes, of course.

142
00:08:14,330 --> 00:08:15,970
I understand your wishes perfectly,
Chairman.

143
00:08:16,670 --> 00:08:18,770
Good. All right.

144
00:08:19,540 --> 00:08:23,570
Stay for dinner. I've asked
the housekeeper to prepare something.

145
00:08:24,180 --> 00:08:25,880
Thank you, sir.

146
00:08:26,810 --> 00:08:30,820
The Chairman seems to be
especially fond of you, Lawyer Kang.

147
00:08:32,180 --> 00:08:35,320
He doesn't usually invite
employees over for a meal.

148
00:08:35,620 --> 00:08:38,360
- You should feel honored.
- Thank you.

149
00:08:38,420 --> 00:08:40,160
Goodness,
you'll give Lawyer Kang indigestion.

150
00:08:40,420 --> 00:08:41,590
Stop chattering and just eat.

151
00:09:22,170 --> 00:09:23,170
Baek Ho.

152
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:28,170
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

153
00:09:39,720 --> 00:09:42,650
Lawyer Kang, please excuse me.
I have to get going.

154
00:09:43,450 --> 00:09:46,490
Don't forget to take your medicine
when you finish eating.

155
00:09:52,730 --> 00:09:54,070
Did you enjoy your meal?

156
00:09:54,270 --> 00:09:55,870
Yes. It was wonderful, thank you.

157
00:09:56,830 --> 00:10:00,000
What's the crest
on Chairman Ma's silverware?

158
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:01,270
You mean this?

159
00:10:13,220 --> 00:10:15,690
This crest is pretty unique.

160
00:10:16,220 --> 00:10:17,760
Is it the Chairman's family crest?

161
00:10:18,360 --> 00:10:19,360
I'm not sure.

162
00:10:20,190 --> 00:10:23,560
I've only heard it's a significant crest
when Dream Department Store was founded.

163
00:10:25,230 --> 00:10:28,170
It’s unusual for the crest to be engraved
on the silverware, isn’t it?

164
00:10:28,800 --> 00:10:29,800
Yes, it is.

165
00:10:29,800 --> 00:10:32,140
I heard it’s a crest passed down
through the Chairman’s family.

166
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:36,310
- I see.
- I guess it's passed down by blood.

167
00:10:36,770 --> 00:10:40,410
Only the Chairman and Seo Rin
use the silverware with that crest.

168
00:10:40,780 --> 00:10:41,950
Is that right?

169
00:10:42,810 --> 00:10:44,250
Anyway, thank you for the meal.

170
00:10:46,950 --> 00:10:47,990
Listen...

171
00:10:48,450 --> 00:10:49,450
Yes?

172
00:10:49,590 --> 00:10:53,560
I guess he still doesn't know
about her marrying General Director Kang.

173
00:10:54,160 --> 00:10:55,330
What am I going to do?

174
00:10:56,360 --> 00:10:59,660
It's nothing.
I was just so happy to see you here.

175
00:11:01,070 --> 00:11:02,330
Me too, Geum Soon.

176
00:11:03,030 --> 00:11:06,200
I can't tell you how reassuring it is
to have you by Jang Mi's side.

177
00:11:07,510 --> 00:11:08,510
Good luck!

178
00:11:13,640 --> 00:11:14,650
(Delete Photo)

179
00:11:16,910 --> 00:11:17,920
(Delete Photo)

180
00:11:29,260 --> 00:11:30,800
This is even harder than getting revenge.

181
00:11:34,030 --> 00:11:36,830
Is this my punishment...

182
00:11:38,040 --> 00:11:39,440
for failing to protect my dad and Seo Rin?

183
00:11:39,440 --> 00:11:40,740
Baek Ho!

184
00:11:41,070 --> 00:11:42,840
Stay with me! Baek Ho!

185
00:11:43,370 --> 00:11:46,810
Please, open your eyes.
Baek Ho, please, wake up!

186
00:11:47,180 --> 00:11:48,310
Baek Ho!

187
00:11:49,550 --> 00:11:50,780
Open your eyes.

188
00:11:52,580 --> 00:11:53,580
I'm sorry.

189
00:11:54,620 --> 00:11:56,150
I'm so sorry, Baek Ho.

190
00:12:01,730 --> 00:12:02,930
Don't waver, Oh Jang Mi.

191
00:12:03,960 --> 00:12:05,730
Do you want Baek Ho to get hurt again?

192
00:12:13,170 --> 00:12:14,170
(Delete Photo)

193
00:12:16,040 --> 00:12:17,140
(Delete Photo)

194
00:12:18,340 --> 00:12:20,880
What? Baek Ho was at the house?

195
00:12:20,980 --> 00:12:22,250
Yes, he was.

196
00:12:22,250 --> 00:12:23,710
I couldn’t help wondering...

197
00:12:23,710 --> 00:12:25,620
what the chairman and he
were talking about in the study.

198
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:27,690
And you didn't hear
what they talked about, Mom?

199
00:12:27,890 --> 00:12:30,720
How could I have?
Secretary Kim was standing guard there.

200
00:12:30,820 --> 00:12:31,990
So I couldn't hear a thing.

201
00:12:34,090 --> 00:12:36,090
They must have talked
about revising the Chairman's will.

202
00:12:37,060 --> 00:12:38,660
Baek Ho's a lawyer, after all.

203
00:12:39,130 --> 00:12:42,400
Why else would the Chairman suddenly call
for a lawyer and his secretary?

204
00:12:42,870 --> 00:12:46,170
- To revise his will.
- You're right.

205
00:12:47,340 --> 00:12:50,010
But how are we supposed to find out
what's in it?

206
00:12:50,370 --> 00:12:51,380
I don't know.

207
00:12:52,980 --> 00:12:56,880
But listen, you have to keep this
from Chae Hwa Young. Understand?

208
00:12:57,250 --> 00:13:00,680
Otherwise, who knows
what she'll pull next.

209
00:13:01,020 --> 00:13:03,420
Mom, are you that afraid of CEO Chae?

210
00:13:03,490 --> 00:13:06,860
I'm doing this for you.
I don't want you caught in the fallout.

211
00:13:09,130 --> 00:13:13,100
Earlier today,
Lawyer Kang was here to see the Chairman.

212
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:18,140
I felt so bad
I couldn't even look him in the eye.

213
00:13:19,440 --> 00:13:22,510
He will feel devastated.
What are you going to do?

214
00:13:22,510 --> 00:13:23,640
Geum Soon.

215
00:13:25,240 --> 00:13:27,610
I think this is my punishment.

216
00:13:29,150 --> 00:13:31,620
I failed to protect my dad,

217
00:13:33,250 --> 00:13:34,950
and this is my only option,

218
00:13:36,120 --> 00:13:37,960
so it must be my punishment.

219
00:13:39,590 --> 00:13:43,030
Don't say that.
Why are you blaming yourself so much?

220
00:13:44,560 --> 00:13:45,600
What am I going to do?

221
00:13:46,430 --> 00:13:48,730
Baek Ho is going to be so hurt.

222
00:13:50,670 --> 00:13:51,900
What am I going to do?

223
00:13:53,470 --> 00:13:56,070
I wish tomorrow would never come.

224
00:13:58,180 --> 00:13:59,380
Geum Soon.

225
00:14:11,660 --> 00:14:13,160
This should be good enough, right?

226
00:14:13,760 --> 00:14:14,760
Ta-da!

227
00:14:16,190 --> 00:14:17,190
What's this?

228
00:14:18,160 --> 00:14:19,160
Here, give me your hand.

229
00:14:23,370 --> 00:14:24,940
It's beautiful.

230
00:14:25,770 --> 00:14:26,770
Put a ring on me too.

231
00:14:38,680 --> 00:14:41,050
Come to think of it, it's been a while
since we've had a proper date.

232
00:14:41,990 --> 00:14:43,690
What can I do to make her happy?

233
00:14:45,490 --> 00:14:46,490
I can't wait.

234
00:14:48,260 --> 00:14:49,260
Baek Ho.

235
00:14:50,290 --> 00:14:51,300
What are you up to?

236
00:14:51,760 --> 00:14:53,560
Nothing. What's up?

237
00:14:54,730 --> 00:14:55,930
Is there something you want to tell me?

238
00:14:56,500 --> 00:14:57,600
About what?

239
00:14:58,170 --> 00:14:59,800
Looks like he doesn't know yet.

240
00:15:00,440 --> 00:15:02,470
Why?
Didn't you come here to tell me something?

241
00:15:03,670 --> 00:15:05,040
No, it's nothing.

242
00:15:06,210 --> 00:15:07,880
How anticlimactic.

243
00:15:10,050 --> 00:15:11,350
Love isn't everything.

244
00:15:11,850 --> 00:15:14,290
- You know that, right?
- Where is this coming from?

245
00:15:15,090 --> 00:15:17,250
You haven't been yourself lately.

246
00:15:17,690 --> 00:15:19,920
And just so you know,
love is everything to me.

247
00:15:29,770 --> 00:15:32,470
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

248
00:15:32,640 --> 00:15:34,840
Ma'am!

249
00:15:34,970 --> 00:15:38,910
I'm here!
Teach me to make your famous kimbap?

250
00:15:39,580 --> 00:15:41,780
Baek Ho's here. I like Baek Ho.

251
00:15:42,410 --> 00:15:43,950
I'm preparing for a date with Jang Mi.

252
00:15:56,990 --> 00:15:58,130
And where are you off to today?

253
00:15:59,300 --> 00:16:02,300
Why?
Do I have to report my every move to you?

254
00:16:03,070 --> 00:16:05,000
Of course you do. You're my daughter.

255
00:16:06,170 --> 00:16:07,670
Are you meeting
General Manager Kang today?

256
00:16:07,670 --> 00:16:09,340
Would you please stay out of my affairs?

257
00:16:10,040 --> 00:16:13,240
Stop getting any funny ideas
and just focus on your wedding plans.

258
00:16:13,440 --> 00:16:14,650
If I want to get married,

259
00:16:14,950 --> 00:16:16,350
it's a necessary step.

260
00:16:16,350 --> 00:16:18,050
I’m only going to let you off the hook
until today.

261
00:16:18,680 --> 00:16:21,120
Don't test me.
You won't like the consequences.

262
00:16:30,690 --> 00:16:33,430
Have you set a wedding date
with the in-laws yet?

263
00:16:33,860 --> 00:16:37,870
Jun Ho's mother said she'll get back to us
with a date that fits her court schedule.

264
00:16:38,940 --> 00:16:42,570
Come on.
A wedding date should bring good fortune.

265
00:16:42,710 --> 00:16:46,740
- How can you just pick any random day?
- What do you know? Stay out of it.

266
00:16:47,310 --> 00:16:50,110
I'll handle Seo Rin's wedding,
so don't you worry about it.

267
00:16:52,450 --> 00:16:56,590
Looks like Seo Rin is off to a date.
Oh, to be young.

268
00:17:01,330 --> 00:17:04,630
That's right. Go have your tearful goodbye
with Kang Baek Ho and get it over with.

269
00:17:04,930 --> 00:17:06,030
Oh Jang Mi.

270
00:17:06,030 --> 00:17:08,270
Grandfather, I'm heading out!

271
00:17:08,430 --> 00:17:11,400
You're about to get married
and still acting like a little kid!

272
00:17:12,440 --> 00:17:14,740
How about I give you some spending money?

273
00:17:15,570 --> 00:17:20,110
Honey! You already gave Seo Rin a building
and extra shares in the company.

274
00:17:20,180 --> 00:17:21,450
Why are you giving her more?

275
00:17:22,050 --> 00:17:24,450
You should give some to our Hong Ju, too.

276
00:17:24,850 --> 00:17:26,580
Here you go.

277
00:17:27,950 --> 00:17:29,320
A little present from me.

278
00:17:29,950 --> 00:17:31,190
Go buy yourself something nice.

279
00:17:32,190 --> 00:17:33,190
But...

280
00:17:36,430 --> 00:17:40,360
- Grandfather!
- Oh my! Why give her so much...

281
00:17:40,560 --> 00:17:42,700
When did you prepare all this?

282
00:17:43,530 --> 00:17:44,700
Don't you have things to do?

283
00:17:45,340 --> 00:17:46,340
Right.

284
00:17:46,870 --> 00:17:48,510
I have a lot to do, like seeing
General Manager Kang's mother...

285
00:17:48,510 --> 00:17:49,610
and getting our wedding clothes fitted.

286
00:18:01,850 --> 00:18:04,220
Okay, this is it. Today is the last day.

287
00:18:05,020 --> 00:18:06,390
Don't let it end in tears.

288
00:18:07,290 --> 00:18:08,830
This is to protect Baek Ho,

289
00:18:09,530 --> 00:18:10,890
and to make sure he'll be happy.

290
00:18:11,900 --> 00:18:12,900
So...

291
00:18:13,900 --> 00:18:15,030
I have to do this with a smile.

292
00:18:23,210 --> 00:18:25,840
What's all this?
You look so beautiful today.

293
00:18:26,240 --> 00:18:29,510
You're the one who said you like it
when I dress like this.

294
00:18:31,350 --> 00:18:32,780
Seriously, you look amazing.

295
00:18:33,350 --> 00:18:35,120
We could just cancel our plans for today.

296
00:18:36,750 --> 00:18:37,820
Oh my.

297
00:18:38,060 --> 00:18:39,120
My girl.

298
00:18:42,330 --> 00:18:43,760
What was that?

299
00:18:44,290 --> 00:18:45,300
Hop in.

300
00:18:48,930 --> 00:18:52,140
- Oh my gosh, really?
- Of course. Hop in.

301
00:19:04,110 --> 00:19:06,250
It feels like forever
since our last date, right?

302
00:19:07,320 --> 00:19:08,320
It really has.

303
00:19:12,360 --> 00:19:13,460
What am I going to do?

304
00:19:14,220 --> 00:19:15,760
How can I possibly...

305
00:19:16,460 --> 00:19:17,630
break your heart?

306
00:19:22,170 --> 00:19:23,200
Why are you looking at me like that?

307
00:19:24,230 --> 00:19:25,500
Is there something on my face?

308
00:19:26,700 --> 00:19:27,700
Let me see.

309
00:19:28,210 --> 00:19:30,410
Maybe it’s because you’ve got "handsome"
written all over your face?

310
00:19:32,080 --> 00:19:34,040
Jang Mi, I didn't know
you had jokes like that in you.

311
00:19:34,310 --> 00:19:35,610
I guess you're rubbing off on me.

312
00:19:36,650 --> 00:19:37,650
Hold on a second.

313
00:19:38,220 --> 00:19:39,380
Where did it go?

314
00:19:41,920 --> 00:19:42,920
A heart.

315
00:19:44,990 --> 00:19:45,990
Come on.

316
00:19:46,560 --> 00:19:49,260
- So cheesy.
- Okay, let's go. We're off.

317
00:19:52,330 --> 00:19:54,570
You're saying
Father is against my marriage?

318
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:57,030
He is.

319
00:19:58,000 --> 00:20:01,810
I feel a little empty
just thinking about you getting married,

320
00:20:02,670 --> 00:20:04,980
so I'm sure your father
feels it even more.

321
00:20:05,740 --> 00:20:08,050
You know how much
he's always doted on you.

322
00:20:08,350 --> 00:20:09,550
I don't get it.

323
00:20:10,380 --> 00:20:12,480
Most parents would kill for their son
to marry into a rich family.

324
00:20:14,350 --> 00:20:16,620
He wouldn't be doing this
if it were Baek Ho, his real son.

325
00:20:18,590 --> 00:20:19,590
Jun Ho.

326
00:20:20,920 --> 00:20:22,590
How could you say that?

327
00:20:22,690 --> 00:20:27,230
Do you really think he's against this
because you were adopted?

328
00:20:28,730 --> 00:20:30,200
That's not it at all.

329
00:20:30,770 --> 00:20:33,900
Have you been feeling this way
all this time?

330
00:20:39,510 --> 00:20:41,510
Your dad is against it...

331
00:20:42,150 --> 00:20:45,150
because he fears they'll look down
on you in that family.

332
00:20:47,420 --> 00:20:49,950
All we want is for you to be happy.

333
00:20:51,360 --> 00:20:52,560
I know that. It's just...

334
00:20:55,090 --> 00:20:56,730
I just can't help thinking that way.

335
00:20:57,790 --> 00:20:58,900
I'm sorry, Mother.

336
00:21:10,940 --> 00:21:12,110
What's this?

337
00:21:13,880 --> 00:21:17,250
Your father and I have been saving this
for you since you were a boy.

338
00:21:17,650 --> 00:21:19,150
We wanted to give it to you
when you got married.

339
00:21:21,990 --> 00:21:23,490
I can't accept this.

340
00:21:24,350 --> 00:21:27,090
You should give it to Baek Ho,
or use it for yourself.

341
00:21:27,320 --> 00:21:30,590
This is your share. Now, take it. Go on.

342
00:21:31,830 --> 00:21:33,860
But you spent so much on my hospital bills
as a kid.

343
00:21:34,030 --> 00:21:36,930
When our son was sick,
money was no object.

344
00:21:39,470 --> 00:21:41,640
All the happiness we felt raising you,

345
00:21:42,170 --> 00:21:43,310
and all our pride.

346
00:21:44,710 --> 00:21:47,080
It's all in here, Jun Ho.

347
00:21:48,310 --> 00:21:49,850
Seeing you grow up so well...

348
00:21:50,550 --> 00:21:52,050
makes me so proud and happy.

349
00:22:03,430 --> 00:22:04,430
Han Young Ja.

350
00:22:04,700 --> 00:22:06,530
What does she think
she's doing with my son?

351
00:22:06,830 --> 00:22:08,330
I'm his mother.

352
00:22:09,730 --> 00:22:12,870
Who does she think she is,
acting like he's her own flesh and blood?

353
00:22:14,340 --> 00:22:17,070
"Seeing you grow up so well
makes me so proud and happy?"

354
00:22:18,110 --> 00:22:19,710
I'm the one who should be saying that.

355
00:22:28,550 --> 00:22:29,550
Here you go.

356
00:22:33,220 --> 00:22:37,630
This is so good.
Jang Mi, you've still got the magic touch.

357
00:22:38,800 --> 00:22:39,800
I know, right?

358
00:22:41,530 --> 00:22:42,570
Hold on a second.

359
00:22:45,370 --> 00:22:49,310
This is my special Kang Baek Ho gimbap,
from a recipe I learned from your mom.

360
00:22:49,810 --> 00:22:52,040
- Try this.
- What? You made this yourself?

361
00:22:52,040 --> 00:22:53,240
Of course I did.

362
00:22:53,910 --> 00:22:56,650
If you marry me,
I can make this for you every day.

363
00:22:56,810 --> 00:22:57,810
Here, try some.

364
00:23:03,490 --> 00:23:04,590
It's delicious, right?

365
00:23:31,210 --> 00:23:32,580
Once we find Seo Rin,

366
00:23:33,320 --> 00:23:35,190
and after the Chairman finds out
about everything,

367
00:23:36,750 --> 00:23:38,020
let's get married then.

368
00:23:39,160 --> 00:23:42,490
Then I'll put a proper ring on your finger
with a huge rock on it.

369
00:23:49,930 --> 00:23:50,930
Here.

370
00:23:53,940 --> 00:23:54,940
Okay.

371
00:24:03,450 --> 00:24:04,450
I know.

372
00:24:05,050 --> 00:24:07,550
I know it took so much for us
to get to this point.

373
00:24:10,620 --> 00:24:11,890
But for the two of us,

374
00:24:12,590 --> 00:24:15,460
if we’re sure about our feelings,
nothing can stand in our way.

375
00:24:19,530 --> 00:24:20,900
Don't cry, Jang Mi.

376
00:24:26,800 --> 00:24:28,210
If I marry you,

377
00:24:29,070 --> 00:24:30,070
I will never,

378
00:24:30,810 --> 00:24:31,810
ever,

379
00:24:33,180 --> 00:24:36,250
make you cry again.

380
00:24:37,810 --> 00:24:39,220
I love you, Baek Ho.

381
00:24:40,380 --> 00:24:41,380
But...

382
00:24:41,920 --> 00:24:43,890
I can't marry you.

383
00:24:44,990 --> 00:24:45,990
I'm sorry.

384
00:24:46,690 --> 00:24:47,690
I'm so sorry.

385
00:25:25,460 --> 00:25:27,200
I wish every day could be like this.

386
00:25:30,930 --> 00:25:33,740
I wish this moment could last forever.

387
00:25:34,240 --> 00:25:35,240
Baek Ho.

388
00:25:39,610 --> 00:25:41,380
Should we sit down here for a bit?

389
00:25:42,150 --> 00:25:43,150
Sounds good.

390
00:25:49,990 --> 00:25:52,960
I'll go get us some coffee.
I wonder where the stand is.

391
00:25:53,020 --> 00:25:54,990
You wait here. I'll be right back.

392
00:26:35,230 --> 00:26:36,600
(Baek Ho, if you're reading this...)

393
00:26:45,510 --> 00:26:47,980
Jang Mi.

394
00:26:48,450 --> 00:26:49,450
Baek Ho.

395
00:26:49,450 --> 00:26:50,450
Jang Mi.

396
00:26:50,450 --> 00:26:51,980
- If you're reading this,
- Jang Mi.

397
00:26:52,880 --> 00:26:53,980
it means that, in the end,

398
00:26:54,580 --> 00:26:58,220
- I couldn't say this to your face.
- Jang Mi.

399
00:26:58,690 --> 00:26:59,690
Jang Mi.

400
00:27:06,600 --> 00:27:07,600
Jang Mi?

401
00:27:08,260 --> 00:27:09,270
Jang Mi.

402
00:27:10,230 --> 00:27:11,230
Jang Mi!

403
00:27:14,370 --> 00:27:15,370
Hey, what are you doing?

404
00:27:16,270 --> 00:27:17,270
I'm sorry.

405
00:27:23,510 --> 00:27:26,950
I'm so happy living as Seo Rin these days.

406
00:27:28,020 --> 00:27:29,620
I get to be as lavish as I want,

407
00:27:30,590 --> 00:27:32,490
and I love that everyone looks up to me.

408
00:27:34,490 --> 00:27:35,990
But when I'm with you,

409
00:27:37,260 --> 00:27:39,100
I'm constantly reminded of the person
I used to be,

410
00:27:39,860 --> 00:27:41,360
the one I want to forget.

411
00:27:42,100 --> 00:27:43,530
And it's agonizing for me.

412
00:27:44,070 --> 00:27:46,070
- The person you called is unavailable.
- So,

413
00:27:46,140 --> 00:27:48,100
- Connecting to voicemail.
- just let me...

414
00:27:50,040 --> 00:27:51,610
live as Seo Rin.

415
00:28:03,190 --> 00:28:04,820
If you love me, let me go.

416
00:28:07,520 --> 00:28:08,590
I'm begging you.

417
00:28:23,770 --> 00:28:25,080
It was fun while it lasted.

418
00:28:26,980 --> 00:28:27,980
Goodbye.

419
00:28:29,350 --> 00:28:30,680
My first man.

420
00:28:56,840 --> 00:28:58,480
(The First Man)

421
00:28:58,580 --> 00:29:00,810
I don't care what anyone says.

422
00:29:01,110 --> 00:29:04,310
- I love you.
- I love you too, Nam Bong.

423
00:29:04,480 --> 00:29:06,420
I'm marrying Jun Ho.

424
00:29:06,680 --> 00:29:10,690
Why are you suddenly marrying my brother?
Of all people, why him?

425
00:29:11,020 --> 00:29:12,620
Stay away from Jang Mi from now on.

426
00:29:13,020 --> 00:29:15,130
I'm no longer Oh Jang Mi
pretending to be Ma Seo Rin.

427
00:29:15,390 --> 00:29:19,200
I've decided to truly live as Ma Seo Rin.
Not a fake, but the real deal.

428
00:29:20,900 --> 00:29:22,900
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
